                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>The pelvic floor consists of muscles, ligaments, and tissues that support the pelvic organs (bladder, uterus, vagina, and rectum).</p>
                  
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <h6>Functions of the Pelvic Floor:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Supports pelvic organs against gravity</li>
                        <li>Helps maintain urinary and fecal continence</li>
                        <li>Contributes to sexual function</li>
                        <li>Stabilizes connecting joints</li>
                        <li>Assists in childbirth</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <h6>Risk Factors for Pelvic Floor Disorders:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Pregnancy and childbirth</li>
                        <li>Aging and menopause</li>
                        <li>Obesity</li>
                        <li>Repetitive heavy lifting</li>
                        <li>Chronic constipation or straining</li>
                        <li>Genetic factors</li>
                        <li>High-impact activities</li>
